      <abstract>In 1906, the United Armenian Calvary Congregational Church formed under the moniker
        "Armenian Presbyterian Church of Troy." After the completion of a church building in 1914,
        the church was separated into the Presbyterian Church and "The Armenian Congregational
        Church of Troy, N.Y." which cooperated closely and worked out of the same church building.
        These churches were reunited in 1919 under their final name, The United Armenian Calvary
        Congregational Church, up until the church was closed in 2020. This collection records the
        activities and membership of this organization through church record books, membership
        records, photograph collections, and financial records.</abstract>
