    <bioghist>
      <head>Historical Note</head>
      <p>The beginning of The United Armenian Calvary Congregational Church in 1906 followed a wave
        of immigration from modern-day Turkey resulting from the Armenian massacres of 1895. The
        church formed under the moniker "Armenian Presbyterian Church of Troy", but after the
        completion of a church building in 1914, the church was separated into the Presbyterian
        Church and "The Armenian Congregational Church of Troy, N.Y." which cooperated closely and
        worked out of the same church building. These churches were reunited in 1919 under their
        final name, The United Armenian Calvary Congregational Church, up until the church was
        closed in 2020. The church operated a sunday school which focused on teaching about Armenian
        heritage and forming connections with Armenian communities throughout the United States.
        Every holiday and season, the church hosted a food kitchen in which feasts were prepared for
        its members. A list of the pastors who served the church follows:</p>
